cted that \uf06413Cbreath of flying bats would converge on the isotopic signature of the C4 sucrose they were fed. Both resting and flying Egyptian fruit bats, indeed, directly fuelled their metabolism with freshly ingested exogenous substrates. The rate at which the fruit bats oxidized dietary sugars was as fast as in 10\uf020g nectar-feeding bats and 5\uf020g hummingbirds. Our results support the notion that flying bats, irrespective of their size, catabolize dietary sugars directly, and possibly exclusively, to fuel flight.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Amitai, O.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Holtze, S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Barkan, S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Amichai, E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Korine, C.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pinshow, B.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Voigt, C. C.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/745b482bd582cfd3faa46d63e79c8b06", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/d43e4a6d128cf966874cf7b658ff09eb20f8beca2f822aeb8b2e91837afa2c9a", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/X4AERX5B", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/X4AERX5B", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/70e263f4dedb9b8665b241650afcb2c4!/b151757-154220", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": 